summary: This is an email chain between FBI personnel discussing logistics for interviews with potential victims of Jeffrey Epstein in West Palm Beach, Florida. The emails coordinate meeting times and availability for victim services.

persons.name: Case Agent
persons.context: The FBI case agent is mentioned as heading to Florida and having interviews scheduled with potential Epstein victims.

events.title: Scheduled victim interviews
events.description: Interviews with potential Epstein victims are scheduled to take place in West Palm Beach, with one at 11 AM and another at 3 PM.

events.title: Case Agent travel to Florida
events.description: The FBI Case Agent is reported to be heading to Florida for the investigation.

keyFacts: FBI personnel were coordinating interviews with potential Epstein victims in West Palm Beach on July 11, 2019.
Interviews were scheduled for 11 AM and 3 PM on that date.
The FBI Case Agent was traveling to Florida for the investigation.
The emails indicate victim services were being offered but no victims had requested services as of that time.
The correspondence shows active FBI investigation into Epstein victims in Florida in July 2019.
